Four People have been injured after three vehicles collided in Wiltshire Road in Marianhill area of Pinetown just after 7 am this morning.Rescue Care Paramedics arrived on the scene of the crashto find that three vehicles had collided blocking the roadway. A total of four people had sustained various injuries and were stabilized on the scene before being transported to various Durban Hospitals for the further care that they required.The exact cause of the collision is unknown however SAPS were on scene and will be investigating further.